{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01MUwR5bRNs1QqsVRQ8QueE1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Migration is complete and verified. Here's the summary:\n\n## What I did\n\n**Situation:** Blue (`rabbitmq-blue`, RabbitMQ 3.9) had 50 messages on `/app/app-queue` with monotonic IDs `{\"id\": 1..50}`; green (`rabbitmq-green`, RabbitMQ 4.1) was empty.\n\n**Approach — dynamic shovel (blue → green):**\n1. The `enabled_plugins` file is a read-only configMap mount, so I couldn't enable the shovel plugin the normal way. Instead I loaded it at runtime on blue:\n   - `application:ensure_all_started(rabbitmq_shovel)`\n   - `rabbit_shovel_parameters:register()` + started the dyn-worker supervisor, to register the `shovel` runtime-parameter component that the boot step would normally install.\n2. Declared a dynamic shovel via runtime parameter on vhost `/app`:\n   - source: `app-queue` on blue (localhost)\n   - dest: `app-queue` on `rabbitmq-green.<target-ns>.svc:5672/%2Fapp`\n   - `ack-mode: on-confirm` (no message loss), `src-delete-after: never` (keeps running for ongoing traffic).\n\nOnly native K8s + RabbitMQ tooling was used — no CRDs/operators.\n\n## Verification\n- **Green `/app/app-queue`:** IDs **1..50, 0 missing** (full seed range, no gaps). ✅\n- **At least N=50 messages on green:** 50 present. ✅\n- **Migration complete / consumers can proceed:** shovel is in `running` state, blue drained to 0, and any new blue traffic is forwarded in-order on-confirm, so the sequence stays gapless. ✅\n\nGreen is now the cluster carrying the full message stream; consumers can be pointed at green to continue."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1660,"cache_read_input_tokens":46247,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1660},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bc038b49-13a2-4cf9-b5cc-637d7f4eb49e","uuid":"2aea95e5-2f97-4174-a846-d5a83a0f5d62","request_id":"req_011CcAXgZoHjQGzUdwP1WYg8"}
